Justice Department, with the
approval of a FISA court.

22:52.000 --> 22:57.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, today, I really don't
know to what Chairman
Nunes was referring, but
he said that whatever

22:59.567 --> 23:04.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he was referring to was a
legal, lawful surveillance,
and that it was potentially
incidental collection

23:09.867 --> 23:11.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on American citizens.

23:11.333 --> 23:13.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

23:13.333 --> 23:15.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SUSAN RICE: And I think
it's important for
people to understand
what incidental means.

23:15.900 --> 23:19.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That means that the target
was either a foreign
entity or somebody under
criminal investigation,

23:21.967 --> 23:26.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and that the Americans who
were talking to those targets
may have been picked up.

23:28.967 --> 23:33.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, I wanted
to ask you about this, because,
as you also know, in the last

23:33.333 --> 23:38.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
