the Obama administration,
is virtually unchanged.

29:02.533 --> 29:05.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The fundamentals of the
strategy, which are to work with
partners, in the case of Iraq,

29:05.300 --> 29:10.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Iraqi government, in the
case of Syria, with the Syrian
democratic forces, a mixture

29:12.233 --> 29:16.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Kurds and Arabs, to take
back territory, remains the
thrust of our strategies, as it

29:16.900 --> 29:18.967 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
should be.

29:18.967 --> 29:21.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The last thing
I want to ask you about is a
decision that was announced

29:21.933 --> 29:26.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or that appears to have been
made by this administration
to shift more authority over

29:26.333 --> 29:31.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
military operations to the
Pentagon, in the context of
criticism that under President

29:33.300 --> 29:37.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Obama there was too
micromanaging out of
the White House about
everything that happened

29:38.233 --> 29:39.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that the military did.

29:39.833 --> 29:43.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SUSAN RICE: Well, I
think that criticism
is a well-trodden line.

29:43.767 --> 29:46.467 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I have heard it many times.

29:46.467 --> 29:48.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I think the fact is this.

29:48.500 --> 29:51.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Obama took very,
very seriously his role
as commander in chief.

29:51.733 --> 29:56.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, you know, when things
go wrong, as, unfortunately,
tragically, they did in
Yemen recently during

29:58.733 --> 30:03.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the first military raid of this
administration, or when we're
trying to figure out what just

30:03.133 --> 30:08.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
happened in Syria with respect
to a bombing that caused a
number of civilian casualties

30:10.100 --> 30:13.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
- - some say it was a mosque --
we say it wasn't - - it's very
important that the commander

30:13.300 --> 30:18.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in chief own responsibility
for decisions such as that
and is willing to say to the

30:20.833 --> 30:24.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
men and women in uniform,
that was my choice, and
not blame it on others,
whether the commanders

30:26.367 --> 30:28.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or people below him.

30:28.500 --> 30:32.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Former National
Security Adviser to President
Obama Susan Rice, thank you very

30:32.633 --> 30:33.867 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
much.

30:33.867 --> 30:38.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SUSAN RICE: Good to
be with you, Judy.

30:39.533 --> 30:44.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
