wrong to sit here at
a confirmation table.

32:13.267 --> 32:18.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think we agree on that,
that it would be a violation
of the independent judiciary

32:20.233 --> 32:24.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for a nominee to a court to
make a promise on any case
in order to win confirmation.

32:24.600 --> 32:26.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

32:26.333 --> 32:27.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
LINDSEY GRAHAM (R),
South Carolina: Are
you an originalist?

32:27.500 --> 32:29.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
NEIL GORSUCH: I'm happy
to be called that.

32:29.833 --> 32:34.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I do worry about the use
of labels in our civic
discussion to sometimes
ignore the underlying

32:37.333 --> 32:41.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
