50:12.100 --> 50:14.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But the algae are very
temperature-sensitive.

50:14.200 --> 50:19.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A few degrees warmer
than normal, and their
photosynthesis is enhanced.

50:19.100 --> 50:24.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
That may sound good,
but the unfortunate
byproduct is a toxin.

50:24.067 --> 50:29.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, the coral is forced to spit
out its food source, revealing
its white color, thus the

50:30.300 --> 50:32.867 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
